HEADWORD: Indiglucin
<hw>In`di*glu"cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Indi</ets>can + <ets>glucin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The variety of sugar (glucose) obtained from the glucoside indican.
It is unfermentable, but reduces Fehling's solution.</def>⟦br⟧
